        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n...right, now all *but* nightly failed. It's always about the docker run of cassandra-init image, which apparently takes too long in some step for docker. It's not obvious to me how to make this more robust though since we don't define any related timeout in the startup script and I can't even find an applicable timeout to redefine in docker run parameters (especially when it's not clear what exactly is taking too long? The image itself is already downloaded when it fails?)",
